-- Chilean Stocks: Besalco, Empresas Hites and Sonda Are Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-03-21T20:09:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/chilean-stocks-besalco-empresas-hites-and-sonda-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:16 p.m. in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index gained 0.1 percent to 4,620.51. The  MSCI
Chile (MXCL)  index advanced 0.1 percent to 2,640.21.  Besalco SA (BESALCO CC), Chile’s second-largest engineering
and construction company, rose 1.6 percent to 953.65 pesos.
Investment in construction projects is accelerating, Finance
Minister Felipe Larrain told an economic forum in Santiago
today.  Empresas Hites SA (HITES)   gained 2.3 percent to 376.31
pesos, the most in three weeks. The department-store operator
had profit of 12.3 billion pesos ($25 million) in 2011 compared
with 11.2 billion pesos the year before, according to a
statement posted on the website of the securities regulator.  Sonda SA (SONDA)   gained 0.5 percent to 1,433.7 pesos in
triple the average volume of the last three months.  Chile ’s
largest information-technology company said it will pay 20.3
billion pesos in dividends, according to a statement on the
website of Chile’s securities regulator. The company was given
the equivalent of buy rating yesterday by Itau BBA Securities
equity analyst Susana Salaru.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
